<div id="wb_element_instance862" class="wb_element" style=" line-height: normal;"><h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:#inherit;"><strong>KNOWING ARGENTINA</strong></span></h3>

<p> </p>

<p> </p>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><span style="background-color: transparent;">WITH THIS TOUR YOU WILL KNOW THE CITY OF BUENOS AIRES, KNOWN AS THE MOST COSMOPOLITAN CITY IN LATIN AMERICA. YOU WILL WALK ON THE RUNWAYS THAT INTO THE FOREST AND YOU WILL SEE THE BEAUTIFUL WATERFALLS OF THE ARGENTINEAN FALLS. YOU WILL BE THRILLED TO SEE THE WHALES FROM PENINSULA VALDEZ GREETING THEM. YOU WILL STAY FRIZZ WHEN CONTEMPLATING THE VASTNESS OF THE PERITO MORENO GLACIER AND SPEND GREAT MOMENTS IN BARILOCHE, KNOWING ITS CIVIC CENTER AND GAZING AT ANYTIME LAKE NAHUEL HUAPI. DO NOT MISS IT!</span></h1>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong style='background-color: transparent; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;'><span style="color: rgb(12, 46, 6); font-family: Batang, serif; font-size: 20px; text-align: justify; text-transform: uppercase; background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h3>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">KNOWING ARGENTINA Ciudad de Buenos Aires | Iguazú | Puerto Madryn | El<br>
Calafate | Bariloche<br>
18 DAYS / 16 NIGHTS</span></strong></h3>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong style="color: rgb(12, 46, 6); font-size: 20px; text-transform: uppercase; background-color: transparent;"><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h3>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The program includes the followind services:</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">* Transfers Airport/ Hotel/ Airport<br>
* 4 nights lodging with breakfast in Buenos Aires.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in Iguazú.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in Puerto Madryn.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in El Calafate.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in Bariloche.<br>
* Excursions in Buenos Aires: A tour of Buenos Aires City. Dinner &amp; Tango Show. Two golfdays.<br>
* Excursions in Iguazú: Excursion to Iguazú Falls on the Argentinean and the Brazilian side.<br>
* Excursions in Puerto Madryn: Excursion to Peninsula de Valdes.<br>
* Excursions in El Calafate: Excursion to Perito Moreno Glacier bridges.<br>
* Excursions in Bariloche: Excursion to Isla Victoria and Arrayan forest. Golf day.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Not Included:<br>
- Domestic or International flights<br>
- Entrances to National Parks</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 1: Europe/America</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">With the Southern Cross Constellation as a guide, you fly over the Atlantic Ocean to have an unforgettable experience in Argentina, with its incredible scenery and wild nature. Enjoy your quiet flight over the ocean to take a rest and to prepare for what comes next.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 2: Marvelous Buenos Aires</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The city tour lets you discover the great city located on the River de La Plata banks. Buenos Aires captures her visitors at first sight, specially its numerous cultural options. “La Reina del Plata” as it was referred to in tango, casts a spell on her guests. Theaters, restaurants, cinemas, bars and coffee shops allow you to discover Buenos Aires’ identity.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 3: Golf day in Buenos Aires</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">After breakfast, you will enjoy a beautiful golf day. Transfer to Hotel. Lodging.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 4: Buenos Aires / Iguazu</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">In Iguazú, nature offers you an unforgettable sight. 900 meters of passages over Rio Iguazu, and the breathtaking Iguazú falls will astonish you.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 5: Iguazú / “Garganta del Diablo” or Throat of the Devil</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">On the “Jungle Train” you begin the ride to the heart of the Iguazú falls. A walk through the passages will allow you to walk among the waterfalls till you reach the “Garganta del Diablo”. The possibility of having a baptism by these spraying waters, on a short trip by boat, is an optional excursion very difficult to resist!</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 6: Brazilian falls</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Enjoy the Iguazú falls from the Brazilian side through 900 meters of passages.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 7: Iguazú / Puerto Madryn</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">A very short flight from Iguazú to Buenos Aires allows you to reach Trelew city, where you begin one of the most surprising adventures: the sightseeing of the Franca Austral Whales in the warm waters of the Golfo Nuevo in front of Puerto Madryn.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 8: Puerto Madryn, adventure in the Peninsula</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">A boat takes you from Puerto Pirámides to the deep blue waters of “Mar Argentino”, where between in the months of July and December the whales arrive to procreate and take care of their little offspring.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 9: Puerto Madryn, penguins</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">You can observe the big colony of Magallanes penguins in Puerto Madryn, that concentrate in the Patagonic coast from October to March, these are one of the treasures that you can enjoy in the excursion to Punta Tombo.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 10: Puerto Madryn – El Calafate</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The Glacier air strokes your face softly as soon as you get off the plane bringing you from Puerto Madryn. You arrive in El Calafate city, the access to the Perito Moreno Glacier.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 11: El Calafate – Perito Moreno Glacier</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">You reach the glacier by walking along the bridges that let you contemplate the magnificent view of the glacier. It is a soundless white river,<br>
with blue tones that wait patiently to fall into the “Argentino Lake”.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 12: El Calafate - Free day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">This region offers lots of options to enjoy The Glaciers National Park.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 13: El Calafate – Bariloche</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">A very short flight from El Calafate allows you to reach one of the most beautiful mountain villages: San Carlos de Bariloche on the Nahuel Huapi Lake.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 14: Bariloche, adventure on the island</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Sailing along the picturesque Nahuel Huapi Lake, you reach Isla Victoria and a dreaming forest of arrayanes trees. This trip begins at “Puerto Pañuelo”, 25 km. from the city, sailing on a very modern boat.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 15: Bariloche – Golf day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">After breakfast, you will enjoy a beautiful day of golf. Transfer to Hotel. Lodging.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 16: Bariloche – Buenos Aires</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The plane brings you back to Buenos Aires. Our package includes a Dinner &amp; Tango Show at Carlos Gardel Corner to discover the secrets of the most famous Argentine dance.</span></strong></h1>

<p> </p>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 17: Buenos Aires, Free day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">After breakfast, you will enjoy a beautiful day of golf. Transfer to Hotel. Lodging.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 18: Buenos Aires, last day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">During your trip you have visited the most stunning regions of this planet. Ezeiza International Airport is your last stop before boarding your international flight. End of our services.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>
